  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db6\u0da0\u0ddc\u0dc0\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dda \u0d85\u0db8\u0d82\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dba\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dd4\u0da7\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Putin does not care about Gorbachev",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Russian President Vladimir Putin will not attend the funeral of the last Soviet leader, Mikhail Gorbachev, Russian media reports.",
        "Kremlin spokesman Dmitry Peskov said Putin would not attend the funeral due to his duties.",
        "Mikhail Gorbachev's funeral will be held tomorrow (2) with full state honours. It will be held in the 'Hall of Columns' hall in the 'House of the Union' building in the capital of Moscow.",
        "91-year-old Mikhail Gorbachev, who had been ill for a long time, died on the 30th. Russian President Putin was the first to issue a condolence message at that time. After that, Gorbachev's body was laid to public honor at the Russian General Hospital, and President Putin went there to pay his respects."
      ],
